i## Algorithms		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThis sound effect plugin will randomly select a channel (corresponding		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ito a speaker) as bass output and the other as treble output. This		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ihappens at plugin load time (usually when the player starts or		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iPulseAudio starts). It prevents unbalanced speaker output if you've		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iused the plugin for too long and a speaker begins to wear.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> Although I don't think this has a high chance of happening, better		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> be safe than sorry.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThe plugin first takes the mean of input sound signal to mix the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isignal to mono channel, since there's not much difference anyway on a		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iportable speaker. Then the signal passes through a low-pass filter,		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iwith the threshold set to the value of `Split Frequency` , to obtain		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ithe bass signal. Treble signal is obtained by subtracting the bass		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
isignal from the input. The low-pass filter implementation is copied		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifrom		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
hLADSPA's Official Examples	URL:https://www.ladspa.org/ladspa_sdk/download.html	{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThen the bass signal is multiplied by `Bass Boost` as enhancement, and		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ioutput to the bass channel. The treble signal goes to the treble		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ichannel without any enhancement.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
